.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="208" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="5.[801,1452,1623,1935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis box="[839,1045,1623,1647]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">Conservation status</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[1079,1279,1623,1647]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hongwae">
<emphasis box="[1079,1279,1623,1647]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">Diospyros hongwae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a restricted geographic range in the form of an EOO and AOO of 
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.63" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" unit="km" value="0.263">0.263 km</quantity>
². It is not known from within any protected area, and is threatened by forest clearing for agriculture, grazing, fire, and exploitation for firewood and construction material, all of which are projected to result in continuing decline. With respect to the principal threat of forest clearing for agriculture, it exists at two locations. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName box="[1169,1289,1847,1871]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="5" pageNumber="208" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hongwae">
<emphasis box="[1169,1289,1847,1871]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="208">D. hongwae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be assessed for its risk of extinction as “Endangered” [EN B1ab(i,ii,iii,iv, v)+2ab(i,ii,iii,iv,v)].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
